title: Collection log/Free-to-play

properties.name: description
properties.value: This article lists items from the collection log that can be obtained on the free-to-play worlds.

content:
This article lists items from the collection log that can be obtained on the free-to-play worlds.

Players that have obtained and kept untradeable items—such as most of the random event rewards—before the introduction of the collection log will have the associated entries completed automatically. However, tradeable items—such as the hill giant club or the stale baguette—have to be obtained again in order to fill the entries.

Last Man Standing[edit | edit source]

There are a total of 10 items and 4 unlocks to collect from the Last Man Standing reward shop. Since competitive mode can no longer be played on free-to-play worlds, players that have not obtained the points before the LMS update can no longer collect the items without playing the minigame on members worlds. While the special attack animation overrides can be bought on free-to-play worlds, they cannot be used by free-to-play players.

Items
Deadman's chest Deadman's legs Deadman's cape
Golden armadyl special attack Golden bandos special attack Golden saradomin special attack
Golden zamorak special attack Victor's cape (1) Victor's cape (10)
Victor's cape (50) Victor's cape (100) Victor's cape (500)
Victor's cape (1000) Swift blade N/A

Other[edit | edit source]

Camdozaal[edit | edit source]

See also: Kudos/Free-to-play

There are a total of 9 items to collect from the Ruins of Camdozaal.

Items
Barronite mace Barronite head Barronite handle
Barronite guard Ancient globe Ancient ledger
Ancient astroscope Ancient treatise Ancient carcanet

Note that ancient relics can be exchanged for kudos by talking to Curator Haig Halen.

Miscellaneous[edit | edit source]

There are a total of 7 miscellaneous items to collect.

Items
Shaman mask Right skull half Left skull half
Top of sceptre Bottom of sceptre Mossy key
Giant key N/A N/A

The miscellaneous items can be obtained as drops from ogress warriors and ogress shamans, the Stronghold of Security NPCs such as minotaurs, flesh crawlers, catablepons and ankou, as well as moss giants and hill giants.

While dragonstone full helm, dragonstone platebody, and dragonstone platelegs can be bought and worn by free-to-play players, they cannot be obtained from the Elven Crystal Chest to complete the collection log entries.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
17 February 2021
(update)

Competitive Last Man Standing mode is no longer available on free-to-play worlds, making it impossible to earn points and collect the associated rewards without membership.

18 November 2020
(update | poll)

The beekeeper's outfit was added to the collection log.

29 August 2019
(update | poll)

Last Man Standing rework introduced a new section of the collection log.

31 January 2019
(update)

Zombie boots were added to the random event group.

13 December 2018
(update)

Random event rewards and the skull sceptre pieces were added to the collection log.

10 December 2018

The collection log was made available to the free-to-play players.
